window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>All Thomas Weaver wanted was death. What he got was time travel. </p> <p>Thomas Weaver, haunted by a teenage tragedy, lived a wasted life. He closed his eyes for what he believed was the last time in 2016, but opened them again in his teenage bedroom and body in 1976. Now a middle-aged man in his teenage body, he sets out to fix everything he did wrong in his first life. A budding serial killer in home room, a possible new romance, and high school algebra complicate his plans.</p> <p>What would you do, if you could do it all again?</p> <p>Includes a special bonus note read by the author.</p>"; 
